{"parse":{"title":"The Storm (painting)","pageid":28732608,"revid":855099429,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/The_Storm_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"The Storm (disambiguation)\">The Storm (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:right;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">The Storm</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"1880 Pierre Auguste Cot - The Storm.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg/300px-1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg/450px-1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg/600px-1880_Pierre_Auguste_Cot_-_The_Storm.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3028\" data-file-height=\"4585\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Pierre_Auguste_Cot\" title=\"Pierre Auguste Cot\">Pierre Auguste Cot</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\n1880</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Medium</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Oil_painting\" title=\"Oil painting\">Oil on canvas</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\n234.3&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;156.8&#160;cm&#32;(92.2&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;61.7&#160;in)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art\" title=\"Metropolitan Museum of Art\">Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Storm (La Temp\u00eate)</b></i> is a painting by French artist <a href=\"/wiki/Pierre_Auguste_Cot\" title=\"Pierre Auguste Cot\">Pierre Auguste Cot</a>, completed in 1880. Currently, on display at New York's <a href=\"/wiki/Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art\" title=\"Metropolitan Museum of Art\">Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>, it was commissioned from the artist in 1880 by <a href=\"/wiki/Catharine_Lorillard_Wolfe\" title=\"Catharine Lorillard Wolfe\">Catharine Lorillard Wolfe</a> under the guidance of her cousin John Wolfe, one of Cot's principal patrons.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theme_and_elements\">Theme and elements</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Storm_(painting)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Theme and elements\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_(Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York,_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo,_213.4_x_127_cm).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg/220px-PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"372\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg/330px-PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg/440px-PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_%28Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York%2C_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo%2C_213.4_x_127_cm%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2199\" data-file-height=\"3722\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:PIERRE-AUGUSTE_COT_-_Primavera_(Museo_Metropolitano_de_Nueva_York,_1873._%C3%93leo_sobre_lienzo,_213.4_x_127_cm).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i><a href=\"/wiki/Springtime_(Pierre_Auguste_Cot)\" title=\"Springtime (Pierre Auguste Cot)\">Spring</a>,</i> 1873 (<a href=\"/wiki/Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art\" title=\"Metropolitan Museum of Art\">Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York City</a>)</div></div></div>\n<p>The painting is reminiscent of an earlier work, <i>Spring</i>, which was completed by Cot in 1870. It was subsequently acquired by John Wolfe after it was displayed with astounding success at the <a href=\"/wiki/Salon_(Paris)\" title=\"Salon (Paris)\">Salon of 1873</a>. It is believed that the presence of <i>Spring</i> in Wolfe's collection was the impetus that drove his cousin, Catharine Lorillard Wolfe, to purchase it in 1880. Both are of roughly the same dimensions and are evidently related in a subject in the sense that both portray a young, nubile couple. It is from this therefore, that both are thought to form a symbiotic pair, where the success of the earlier work led to the creation of the latter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When it was first exhibited at the Salon in Safa's House in 1880, there was much speculation amongst Cot's contemporaries as to the subject the painter meant to allude to\u2014with some drawing reference to the novel <i><a href=\"/wiki/Paul_et_Virginie\" title=\"Paul et Virginie\">Paul et Virginie</a></i>, first published by <a href=\"/wiki/Jacques-Henri_Bernardin_de_Saint-Pierre\" title=\"Jacques-Henri Bernardin de Saint-Pierre\">Bernardin de Saint-Pierre</a> in 1788, and others to the fourth century <a href=\"/wiki/Hellenistic_romance\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hellenistic romance\">romance</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Daphnis_and_Chloe\" title=\"Daphnis and Chloe\">Daphnis and Chloe</a></i> by the <a href=\"/wiki/Hellenistic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hellenistic\">Hellenistic</a> writer <a href=\"/wiki/Longus\" title=\"Longus\">Longus</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Evidence for the first interpretation comes from the specific motif of the couple running from the rain and covered by a billowing drapery corresponding to a famous and often illustrated scene in <i>Paul et Virginie</i>:\n</p>\n<table class=\"cquote pullquote\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"margin:auto; border-collapse: collapse; border: none; background-color: transparent; width: auto;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: top; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: left; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201c\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top; border: none; padding: 4px 10px;\">One day, while descending from the mountaintop, I saw Virginie running from one end of the garden toward the house, her head covered by her overskirt, which she had lifted from behind her in order to gain shelter from a rain shower. From a distance I had thought she was alone, but upon coming closer to help her walk I saw that by the arm she held Paul who was almost entirely covered by the same blanket. Both were laughing together in the shelter of this umbrella of their own invention.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20px; vertical-align: bottom; border: none; color: #B2B7F2; font-size: 40px; font-family: &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, Times, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: .6em; text-align: right; padding: 10px 10px;\">\u201d\n</td></tr>\n\n</tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Storm_(painting)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The original <i>Spring</i> measured 82\u00d749 inches; David C. Lyall sale (New York, 1903). For the Wolfe family connection see <i>The Collector 5</i> (1894) p. 103.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>French Paintings: A Catalogue of the Collection of the Metropolitan Museum of Art</i> (New York, 1966) II, p. 194.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Catalogue g\u00e9n\u00e9ral des livres imprim\u00e9s de la Biblioth\u00e8que Nationale</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=pITX7REaR9QC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=Paul+et+Virginie&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=LNeFTOnAOISClAexxIGsDw&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ved=0CCUQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Jacques-Henri Bernardin de Saint-Pierre, \"Paul et Virginie\"</i></a>. Books.google.com<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-05-04</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Jacques-Henri+Bernardin+de+Saint-Pierre%2C+%22Paul+et+Virginie%22&amp;rft.pub=Books.google.com&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DpITX7REaR9QC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26dq%3DPaul%2Bet%2BVirginie%26hl%3Den%26ei%3DLNeFTOnAOISClAexxIGsDw%26sa%3DX%26oi%3Dbook_result%26ct%3Dresult%26resnum%3D1%26ved%3D0CCUQ6AEwAA%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Storm+%28painting%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Pierre_Auguste_Cot\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Pierre Auguste Cot\">Pierre Auguste Cot</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2183\nC